history.content:
Depending on your skills, interests, and how seriously you're planning to take these classes, I wouldn't really recommend taking either of those alongside 189, but it's definitely doable.  


I think 182 and 184 individually are less workload than 162 (which I have taken), but more workload than 161 or 186 (but I haven't taken either of these). 

I think 189 is much higher workload and much more difficult than 170; I took 184 and 170 the same semester as a sophomore and felt the workload was very high. 

I took 182 and 189 concurrently, and did very well in 182 but I took 189 with a very strong P/NP mentality. 

That being said, 182 and 184 are both project-based classes so theoretically pair well with the more pset heavy 189. I think 182 gives you slightly more break time in between projects. You may prefer 182 if you have more comfort with Python and pytorch/tensorflow, or 184 if you have more comfort with C++ or C-style languages.

Hi, can anyone please give me some insights on the workload and difficulty of CS182 and CS184? 

I've taken 161, 186, 162, 170 and registered for 189 in Spring. Thank you!
history.subject: 182 and 184 Workload
